{{refimprove|date=May 2009}} {{Infobox Convention | name = Itzacon Eire | image = [[Image:Itzaconeirebanner2005.gif]] | caption = | status = Defunct | genre = Gaming | venue = [[National University of Ireland, Galway]] | location = [[Galway]] | country = [[Ireland]] | first = 2005 | last = | organizer = FanSci [http://www.fansci.nuigalway.ie] | filing = | website = http://www.itzacon.com and [http://irishgamingwiki.com/wiki/Itzacon] }} '''Itzacon Eire''', more popularly known as Itzacon (not to be confused with ''Itzacon'', a defunct Sci Fi convention formerly held in Texas) is the premier [[gaming convention]] run by the [[Fantasy and Science Fiction Society]] (Fansci) of [[NUI Galway]], [[Ireland]].
==History== Itzacon Eire was founded in 2005<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20041116120025/http://www.itzaconeire.com/ Itzacon I website at Archive.org]</ref> by [[Anita Murray]],<ref>[http://irishgamingwiki.com/wiki/Anita_Murray Anita Murray at Irishgamingwiki.com]</ref> then Auditor of the Society. As of 2015 it has been run for eleven years successfully and looks to continue in that vein into its second decade.
In 2007 it established the [[National Game Writers Award]]. This award is for [[Role-playing game]] and [[LARP]] writers who have shown a continued dedication to the Irish convention scene and have produced material of noted quality for Itzacon Eire.
